{
  "texts": [
    "Setting d to be the value of the conditional density function at Q 1 ' before applying these changes and using this as the denominator for calculating the k values for each Q j after applying the changes accounts for this problem.",
    "When this scenario occurs, it may break the relationship that k j ≥ q.",
    "However, it still holds that k j ≥ 0.",
    "Additionally, the corresponding N+1 solutions may not have their corresponding k values in descending order after these changes, so they are reordered so that their k values are in descending order.",
    "Quantities are measured in kts and country abbreviations follow the ISO-3166-1 3-letter country codes."
  ]
}